      "content": "You're right, the chaos and instability that followed the intervention do raise questions about its success. The US and its allies' support for the Libyan rebels did ultimately lead to a power vacuum, which extremist groups like ISIS exploited to establish a stronghold. In hindsight, the intervention may have been premature and overly optimistic about the ability of the Libyan people to govern themselves. A more nuanced assessment might conclude that the intervention was a strategic mistake, as it created the conditions for the very instability it aimed to prevent.",
